## 2. Color Palette & Roles

Define semantic role first, then the value. Hex literals never appear in markup — only CSS variables.

| Token | Hex | Role |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-bg` | `#FAF7F2` | Base canvas |
| `--color-surface` | `#FFFFFF` | Elevated surface (cards) |
| `--color-surface-2` | `#F1ECE3` | Secondary surface |
| `--color-border` | `#E5DFD3` | Hairlines, dividers |
| `--color-text` | `#1C1A17` | Primary text |
| `--color-text-muted` | `#6B6359` | Secondary text |
| `--color-accent` | `#B8472A` | Primary accent (CTA, highlights) |
| `--color-accent-hover` | `#9C3A21` | Accent hover state |
| `--color-focus-ring` | `#B8472A` | Keyboard focus outline |

**Rules:**
- Dominant: `--color-bg` + `--color-text`. ~85% of the page.
- Accent appears on no more than ~5% of any viewport.
- Never use the accent for body copy or large surfaces.

